This paper discusses the factors related to the quality of the user experience in ubiquitous recommender systems, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also proposes a new hybrid recommendation model, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and deep learning (cs.DL). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of mobile devices, which can be categorized under cybernetics (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
